{
  "texts": [
    "a) One of the urgent issues is the data space shift.",
    "The data acquisition protocol changes, sensor configuration changes, etc.",
    "will lead to variations in collected healthcare data, thus the HFMs trained for the original data will be unable to adapt to the new data form.",
    "b) The heterogeneity of the outcomes will occur when data are sampled from different subjects, contexts, population groups, etc., making the target shift in HFMs.",
    "For example, the incidence of different diseases would change along with personal characteristics and behaviors [388], such as genetic diseases, smoking, eating habits, etc., so that it will extremely limit the HFMs' ability in the personalized and precise medical care."
  ]
}